<h2>Risk scoring and intervention triggers</h2>

<p>Signal detection without a scoring system creates alert fatigue. The goal is a composite risk score that tells your team where to intervene, in what order of priority, and with what motion. Below is a three-tier intervention framework with score ranges and corresponding actions.</p>

<div class="trigger-grid">
  <div class="trigger-card tier-green">
    <div class="trigger-header"><div class="dot"></div> Tier 1 — Healthy (70-100)</div>
    <div class="trigger-body">
      <p><strong>Profile:</strong> On-track activation, strong champion engagement, utilization at or above contracted level.</p>
      <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Expansion readiness. Begin identifying expansion signal and initiating value conversations.</p>
      <div class="action">Scheduled QBR cadence. Expansion playbook initiated at month 4 if utilization &gt;85%.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="trigger-card tier-amber">
    <div class="trigger-header"><div class="dot"></div> Tier 2 — Watch (40-69)</div>
    <div class="trigger-body">
      <p><strong>Profile:</strong> One or more leading signals below threshold. Trajectory is degrading but relationship is intact.</p>
      <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Targeted intervention within 7 days. Do not wait for a lagging signal to confirm the risk.</p>
      <div class="action">CSM-led diagnostic call. Identify root signal. Executive sponsor loop-in if champion engagement is the trigger.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="trigger-card tier-red">
    <div class="trigger-header"><div class="dot"></div> Tier 3 — At Risk (&lt;40)</div>
    <div class="trigger-body">
      <p><strong>Profile:</strong> Multiple high-weight signals below threshold or a single critical signal (champion departure, stalled activation) confirmed.</p>
      <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Executive-led save play within 48 hours. Assign a dedicated recovery plan with 30-day milestones.</p>
      <div class="action">Leadership escalation. Cross-functional recovery plan. Success plan reset if onboarding is the root cause.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

